value.0: The Living Guard are renowned for their skill, and despite the state of their former home, they remain dangerously organized.

This helmet has been exquisitely forged from adamantine, its sinisterly beautiful design typical of drow craftsmanship. A small letter "V" has been interwoven into the pattern upon the visor.

Adamantine is an extraordinarily hard alloy that is almost impenetrable to normal weapons. Deposits of adamant are usually found near areas of Faerzress in the Underdark, and to the Deep Denizens it is usually black in colour, though it possesses a green sheen when viewed by natural light or a purple-white sheen when viewed by magical light.

The cauchemar is a horrible, especially malevolent version of a nightmare. The sight of one of these great horrors bearing down is enough to shake the heart of the boldest champion.

A cauchemar nightmare is about the size of a light war horse.
A sailor who will handle your travel arrangements.
This dwarven woman seems to be obsessing over the nearby sewer grate, a look of perplexity upon her features.
When an ordinary lantern just won't do it, this lantern seems of high quality and craftsmanship.

Value.value: Ah, you have the look of someone in need of a task.
Something's gone wrong below and if we don't sort it we'll be up to our eyeballs in muck.
Return with proof that you've gotten to the bottom of this and I'll kick some gold your way.
There seems to be a malfunction in the sewage processing mechanism. The various fluids that keep the machine running are somehow moving on their own.
Any luck finding the source of the issue? Machine access should be at the south end of the western sewer.
A malfunctioning maintenance golem? Odd. They're normally quite docile. Well, here's your reward! Thanks for the help.
The sanitation guildmaster should hear about this. I already dread the paperwork.

A shovel is ideal for moving quantities of dirt from one location to another.  Other uses are possible, of course.
Useful for carrying water, fruit, liquids, cleaning supplies, or pretty much anything that will fit inside of it, the bucket has been a utilitarian object for many, many years.

This dark skinned Elf sells bags and boxes of all sorts and sizes.
A black robe.  Fine for walking about town, and being seen at the Nomad.  Not very practical for battle however.
A gruff-looking merchant with a heavy brow. He regards you shrewdly.
This pale elven man seems to have a look of worry plastered on his face. He constantly looks out to the West, as though hoping for something to arrive.
When an ordinary lantern just won't do it, this lantern seems of high quality and craftsmanship.

Value.value: Pardon me, are you headed east toward the bay by chance?
My husband is surveying the southeastern bay, you see, and didn't make it home last night.
Could you put my mind at ease and get proof that he's doing just fine?
If you have any trouble convincing him that I sent you, tell him you "wouldn't be caught dead in those slippers". He'll know what it means!
I would go myself, but the wildlife can be rather dangerous just off the road.
Have you found my husband? As a surveyor, he tends to move around a lot. Check every nook and cranny!
D-dead? By the gods, I-.. I need a moment. Just.. keep the ring. He'll have no use of it now.
My poor Ranholt. What will I do now?

value.0: A street rat, but seemingly on a mission for his master.

Value.value: Hello! Oh, you got a grocery list from Hendrik? Thank you! I'll make sure to get everything on it!

value.0: This woman appears very busy, keeping track of ships and taking docking fees.

Value.value: *looks up from her notes* Yes? Oh, his docking status? *looks over some papers* His ship is cleared and fees are paid. *before you can respond, the woman is already busy elsewhere*

value.0: Standing tall and imposing, this golem is sculpted entirely from the gleaming, jet-black depths of obsidian, its surface polished to a mirror-like sheen. It gives off a slight warmth as though burning with the heart of the nearby volcano.

Value.value: *This construct is as motionless as a statue.*
